</paragraph>
<paragraph id="670633474014466AFF76875CEB58B34B" blockId="12.[163,779,630,806]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF76875CE81BB2E1" box="[163,294,631,652]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small- to medium-sized haustoriids (
<quantity id="A0419EA24014466AFF7F87BEE838B2C6" box="[170,261,661,683]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="2.0">2–7 mm</quantity>
). Maxilla 2 outer lobe narrow, lanceolate (except in 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFF6B879EE818B2A4" authorityName="Hancock &amp; Wicksten" authorityYear="2018" box="[190,293,692,714]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Haustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allardi">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF6B879EE818B2A4" box="[190,293,692,714]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">L. allardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), roughly twice size of inner lobe. Maxilliped baler lobe weakly developed. Pleon slightly overhanging urosome; epimeron 3 smooth, ventrally curved (without hook). Telson cleft emarginate or to base.
</paragraph>
